captions.text: Hi guys.
I'm Meredith Foster.
I'm 16 years old.

And you might know me as
StilaBabe09 on YouTube.

I make beauty videos and fashion
videos, and tips and

tricks for young girls on
how to feel confident
in their own skin.

I have about 180,000 subscribers
and around 15

million videos views
on my channel.
[APPLAUSE]

So my first video on YouTube was
actually a contest entry.

And I did a mermaid look
for Halloween.

And she liked my video, and she
gave me Honorable Mention,
which is really awesome.

And I was super excited
about that.

And then she gave me a couple
shout-outs on Twitter.

And some people commented on my
video, say hey, you should
film some more videos.
So that's how I started.

So one of my favorite videos
that I actually have on my

channel is my Taylor Swift
inspired curls.

It has about a million
views on YouTube.

And I think it's so popular,
because everyone loves
Taylor's hair.
And they are trying to get it.
[SCREAMS]

So when I posted that, I thought
it's going to get the
normal views.

But it kind of just exploded,
and everyone was freaking out

about it, and saying
oh, it's so cool.

It is using no heat and
that's just the most
amazing thing about it.

I used to want to be
a veterinarian,
because I love animals.
I have a black lab.

And I just really like being
around animals and
taking care of them.

But as of right now, I'm not
really sure, so just
playing it by ear.

So one thing my viewers may
not know about me is that

instead of dipping my Chips Ahoy
cookies in milk like a

normal person, I actually dip
it in water, let it silk--
silk? set?
soak.

I let it soak in there for about
a minute until it gets
nice and soggy.

And then I actually take my
spoon, and scoop it out and
then eat it.
Mmm.
Mmm-hmm.

I'm just myself when
I'm on camera.

I don't try to act
a certain way.
And they just like my ideas.
And I give them good tips.

So right now, Amy and I are
going to be showing you how to

put together some fashionable
back-to-school outfits, using

affordable pieces, all from
the Salvation Army.

And hopefully this gives you
guys some ideas on your fall

wardrobe and back-to-school
outfit ideas.

And it's just really fun to
be friends with them.

I'm friends with
a lot of them.
So it's really fun.

So my username actually
originated from my favorite

make-up brand in
2009 was Stila.

So I decided I wanted to have
that name as my first part of
my user name.

And then Babe was kind of
just like a filler.

I just needed something
to sound--
to flow.
And then 09--

nine is my favorite number, and
I've used that for like my

sports jerseys when I played
volleyball and lacrosse.

So it's my favorite number, and
I decided to just add that
on the end.

I don't know why nine is my
favorite number, because I

really like getting first
in everything.

I'm really competitive, so you
guys better watch out.

Thank you guys for watching
Dance Showdown.
Hopefully you enjoyed.

Make sure to thumbs
up this video and
subscribe to the channel.

And I will talk to you
in my next video.
Bye guys.
[MUSIC PLAYING]
